channel.title: Packet Loader?
channel.description:
Hello i played a game called [s]Habbo[/s] its rubbish now thought :) there was this thing .. packet loader or something and when you load habbo and say walk around in the packet loader all this code comes up and if you put a code in you can get serverside glitched ect.. seen as habbo only has around 20k players and runescape has 300k+ or w.e i was thinking someone out there would know about a packet loader thing is there one for runescape? am i missing out on something?
If i am please can you tell me a link to the download location.

item.title: Packet Loader?
item.dc:creator: @Uriko Uriko
item.description:
@Uriko wrote:

Lmao, you’re from the UK, aren’t you?

Bots do this now, and always have, they send packets to the runescape servers. But it’s not like you can send a packet for something that doesn’t exist in your say… inventory… and expect to actually have the [item] there. It just doesn’t work like that.
